# The window object is not available in Node. The window object is a reference to the browser window.
# The window object is provided by the Chrome runtime when V8 is running in the Chrome browser.
# The NodeJs runtime has a comparable feature, a variable called global.
global

# The browser also has the document which allows viewing and manipulating the DOM.
# The NodeJs corresponding item is process.
# process provides access to various Node properties and methods which enable manipulation of the Node process.
process

NodeJS uses the Chrome V8 engine to run JavaScript.
NodeJS extends the JavaScript language by providing C++ bindings to V8.
This enables JavaScript to do anything that C++ can do. E.G C++ can access the file system so JavaScript running on NodeJs can now access the file system.








